---
description: FastAPI, Python, domain, persistence, and worker rules
globs:
  - "apps/api/**/*.py"
  - "apps/worker/**/*.py"
  - "tests/**/*.py"
alwaysApply: false
---

Use Python 3.12+, strict typing, Pydantic v2, SQLAlchemy 2, and Alembic.

Respect boundaries:
- domain: pure business logic;
- application: use cases and ports;
- infrastructure: vendors, database, queue, providers;
- interfaces: HTTP, webhook, CLI, worker entry points.

Every tenant-owned query is tenant-scoped.
No provider payload types in domain code.
No raw message content in logs.
External operations require timeout, bounded retry, and idempotency where relevant.
Tests must not call paid APIs by default.
